cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper proposes a deep-neural-network-based detection system for lung nodule detection in computed tomography (CT), which involves computer vision and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of deep reconstruction network and convolutional neural network, which are common techniques in deep learning and machine learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. The paper also involves optimization techniques, such as primal-dual optimization, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper is related to medical imaging, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
